    </mrow>
    <mo>=</mo>
    <mn>1</mn>
   </math>
  </alternatives>
 </inline-formula> is equivalent to zero spatial correlation and called complete spatial randomness (CSR). Target cells are aggregated more than CSR when 
 <inline-formula id="pcbi.1005952.e006">
  <alternatives>
   <graphic xlink:href="pcbi.1005952.e006.jpg" id="pcbi.1005952.e006g" mimetype="image" position="anchor" orientation="portrait" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink"/>
